title: Implement OpenAI Codex OAuth login and refresh flow
---
## Requirements

- Implement the OpenAI Codex PKCE OAuth flow based on the Roo-Code/OpenClaw references.
- Generate verifier/challenge + state, open the browser to `https://auth.openai.com/oauth/authorize`, and support localhost callback capture on port `1455`.
- Provide a manual pasteback fallback for remote/headless sessions when the callback cannot complete automatically.
- Exchange codes at `https://auth.openai.com/oauth/token`, persist refreshable credentials, and implement refresh with expiry handling and invalid-grant detection.
- Extract and retain `ChatGPT-Account-Id` (or equivalent account identifier) from returned JWT claims when available.

## Acceptance Criteria

- A successful login produces persisted Codex OAuth credentials with expiry metadata.
- Expired credentials refresh automatically and preserve rotated refresh tokens.
- Headless/manual fallback is supported without requiring a local callback.
- Error messages are actionable for revoked/expired credentials.
